---  
description: Use when creating or validating Sitecore __Standard Values, insert options, default field values, or deciding how folder, parent, and child templates should behave.  
alwaysApply: false  
---  
  
`__Standard Values` are mandatory for every custom template.  
  
Creation rule:  
- `__Standard Values` is a child of the template item.  
- Its name must be exactly `__Standard Values`.  
- Its `templateId` must be the parent template's own ID.  
  
Pattern:  
- create_content_item(name="__Standard Values", templateId="<template-id>", parentId="<template-id>")  
  
Three scenarios:  
  
1. Folder templates  
- Set `__Masters` to the datasource template IDs allowed inside the folder.  
- Example: folder allows parent datasource items.  
  
2. Parent datasource templates with children  
- Set `__Masters` to child template ID(s).  
- Also set default values for parent fields.  
- Required for Pages Content tab "Add" behavior.  
  
3. Simple datasource templates or child templates  
- Set meaningful default values for fields.  
- No `__Masters` unless the template itself should allow children.  
  
Guidelines:  
- Text fields: use sensible placeholders or `$name`  
- Rich Text: use minimal HTML placeholder  
- General Link: use complete Sitecore link XML  
- Image: leave empty or use placeholder media item  
- Checkbox: `"1"` or `""`  
  
Useful tokens:  
- `$name`  
- `$date`  
- `$time`  
- `$now`  
- `$id`  
- `$parentid`  
- `$parentname`  
  
If insert options are missing, check the template's `__Standard Values` first.  
If new items are blank, check default values on `__Standard Values`.  